m-and-nubia/#preface">Preface</a></span></li><span style="font-size: x-small;">     </span><li class="level1" style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section1">1.</a> Introduction      </span><ul><li class="level2"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section1.1">1.1.</a> Before Aksum and Kush </span></li><li class="level2"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section1.2">1.2.</a> The First Millennium BCE: A Turning Point in State Formation</span></li></ul></li><span style="font-size: x-small;">   </span><li class="level1" style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section2">2.</a> The Question of Aksumite Trade with Nubia</span></li><span style="font-size: x-small;"> </span><li class="level1" style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section3">3.</a> The Third Century CE: <i>Monumentum Adulitanum II</i> (RIE 277)    </span><ul><li class="level2"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section3.1">3.1.</a> Cosmas Indicopleustes at Adulis</span></li><li class="level2"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section3.2">3.2.</a> Dating <i>Monumentum Adulitanum II</i></span></li><li class="level2"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section3.3">3.3.</a> Aksumite Expansion in Northeast Africa            </span><ul><li class="level3"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/awdl/isaw/hatke2013-aksum-and-nubia/#section3.3.1">3.3.1.</a> Aksum and Rome’s Southern Frontier</span></li><li class="level3